{{Frame
|Comments=Refers to representation and decision-making in the domain of governance and government, specifically.

Entered per the request after the April 2014 site visit.

The institutionalized process that enables the governed to make decisions about their representation, whether through a representative body or directly.

This includes voting and the campaigns and elections surrounding voting.

In a democracy, things are decided by vote, not by force.
